  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dba\u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dba \u0db4\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dbb\u0dda\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dda \u0d85\u0db0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dab \u0dc0\u0ddb\u0daf\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0db4\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dab\u0dba\u0da7 80,000\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dba \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "80,000 has been spent on the forensic examination of the dead mason",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is reported that residents of Uduvahinna village in Udadumbara Mahawala will spend 80,000 rupees for the forensic medical examination of a dead mason.",
        "The body of this bricklayer who died suddenly near his home was taken to Udadumbara hospital in a Malshalawaka vehicle, but since there was no forensic doctor, the body was taken back to Theldeniya Base Hospital. The relatives of the family say that the forensic doctor of that hospital had to be brought to the Udambara hospital again because he was on leave.",
        "80,000 rupees had to be paid for these traveling expenses and the villagers have arranged to collect that amount instead of that amount to the residents."
      ],
